        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 8:30PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 829 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Salineno, or 8 miles northwest of Roma, moving west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rio Grande City, Roma, Escobares, El Sauz, La Rosita, Los Alvarez,
Fort Ringgold County Park, Garceno, Falcon Dam, and Starr County
Sheriffs Office.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
